				<h3>About Gloria</h3>
				<p>Gloria L. Paniagua, painter and lawyer was born in Medellin,
					Colombia. She has been painting for more than 30 years. Her
					beginnings were figuration, semi-figuration and abstraction
					techniques of mixed collage in acrylic on canvas. After arriving to
					New York more than 16 years ago she started working in oil on
					canvas, where she still continues working. Her paintings have gone
					through different stages in her career. Its theme has always been
					with a social, cultural and spiritual context where the human being
					has always been the main character in her work, of course with a
					contemporary concept and cutting-edge. Today, her way of expressing
					the human being is more abstract. This touches metaphysical themes
					where in her paintings color plays a very important role that
					determines the harmony of the different light reflections that
					contrasts the shadows of bright colors where there is a connection
					with spirituality - light and life. And where the deep color marks
					the fear and sadness - descending to death and the afterlife. In
					other words, her abstract painting is the use of language without
					shape with chromatic freedom that expresses through color different
					astral states of the human being. Also, in addition to paintings,
					Gloria makes sculptures with the use of clay.</p>
